Oby Ezekwesili, a former minister of education, has been appointed to chair the transition committee of Charles Soludo, governor-elect of Anambra state. In a statement issued on Thursday, Joe Anatune, media aide of Soludo, said the committee would be inaugurated on January 20. “This is to announce the constitution of a transition committee which will liaise with a team set up by the government of Anambra state to ensure a seamless transition from the Governor Willie Obiano’s administration to a Chukwuma Charles Soludo-led administration as from 17th March 2022,” the statement reads. “The full terms of reference for the committee as well as its mode of operation will be communicated during the inauguration/first plenary sessions scheduled for 19- 22nd January, 2022 at the Golden Tulip (Agulu Lake) Hotel, Anambra state. “Members are expected to arrive on Wednesday, 19th while the inauguration and first plenary sessions start on the 20th. Departure is on the 23rd.” Here is the full list; 